The key insight from real analysis is that uniform convergence implies convergence in the integral. Since `fₙ` converges uniformly to `F` on `[a, b]`, for any `ε > 0`, we can find an `N` such that for all `n ≥ N`, `|fₙ(x) - F(x)| < ε/(b-a)` for all `x ∈ [a, b]`.

